ENTRY            D4438   20260129   20260508   20260508       D151
SUBENT        D4438001   20260129   20260508   20260508       D151
BIB                 10         35
TITLE      Low-energy measurement of the 86Kr(a,n)89Sr reaction
           cross section and its impact on weak r-process
           nucleosynthesis
AUTHOR     (G.G.Kiss,S.R.Kovacs,T.N.Szegedi,P.Mohr,F.Montes,
           A.Arcones,A.Toth,A.Nemeth,E.Szilagyi,M.Kumar Pal,
           M.Braun,Z.Halasz,Z.Elekes,G.Gyurky,T.Szucs)
INSTITUTE  (3HUNDEB,3HUNKOS)
REFERENCE  (J,AJ,988,170,2025)
           #doi:10.3847/1538-4357/ade4c9
FACILITY   (CYCLO,3HUNDEB)
SAMPLE     Natural isotopic composition Kr gas cell target with
           10.02 mm length and 10 torr pressure.
DETECTOR   (SIBAR)
METHOD     (ACTIV) Cross section was measured by using charged
           particle activation method.
           (BSPEC) Activity measurement of the reaction products
           was done by Beta ray spectrometry based on Partially
           Depleted Silicon Surface Barrier Detector.
ERR-ANALYS (EN-ERR)
           The total uncertainty of the energy values 4.09% is
           estimated using the standard method, which involves
           taking the quadratic sum of the independently
           contributing parameters: beam energy (0.3%), energy
           loss calculations (4%), entrance foil thickness (0.8%)
           (ERR-T)
           The total uncertainty of the cross-section values
           13-17% is estimated using the standard method, which
           involves taking the quadratic sum of the independently
           contributing parameters.
           (ERR-S,8.,12.) statistical uncertainty (8-12%)
           (ERR-1) beam intensity (3%)
           (ERR-2) detection efficiency (8%)
           (ERR-3) implantation probability calculation (3%)
           (ERR-4,5.,8.) number of target atoms (5-8%)
HISTORY    (20260129C) TT
ENDBIB              35
